    "attributes": {
        "action": "Introduce a Product Redundancy Tax.",
        "additional_details": "To encourage industry to think about the environmental effects of their products and packaging and to discourage development of designed in obsolescence.  For example, if a product is disposable then add a 100% Tax to the cost price. If 50% then 50% tax and so on. All tax raised to be used to subsidise Local authority costs of collection and disposal of waste.",
        "background": "On the principle that the \u2018Polluter Pays\u2019 introduce a product redundancy tax based on how repairable a product is and how much of the packaging is recyclable.",
